1
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:05,960
(Coming up)
Let me ask you something.

2
00:00:05,960 --> 00:00:07,040
If you get those sets,

3
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:09,400
(Here comes the guilt trip)
you wouldn't keep them all, right?

4
00:00:09,540 --> 00:00:09,980
(Ning thinks it over)

5
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:11,520
(Of course he wouldn't)
Ning wouldn't do us like that.

6
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:12,640
Of course I wouldn't.

7
00:00:12,640 --> 00:00:14,440
(He knows his title)
What am I to you guys? Good big bro.

8
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:15,340
Our dad.

9
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:17,560
No, wait.

10
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:18,400
This big bro is slick.

11
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:19,240
(Speaking of big bros)
Wait, we have a new big bro.

12
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:21,120
Me? Big Bro "Xin"?

13
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:22,440
(Big Bro Xin)
Right. Big Bro No. 2.

14
00:00:22,440 --> 00:00:24,240
Big Bro No. 2.

15
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:26,760
(Thoughtful water service)
Cheers.

16
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:28,760
We can't let Big Bro Xin serve us.

17
00:00:28,760 --> 00:00:29,520
(Thoughtful Big Bro Xin)
Thanks, Big Bro Xin.

18
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:30,880
Thanks, Big Bro Xin.

19
00:00:30,980 --> 00:00:31,680
(Time to eat)

20
00:00:31,680 --> 00:00:34,480
Ding, what's the craziest mission
you'd be willing to do?

21
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:36,280
Like, what's your nightmare difficulty?

22
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:37,120
Probably

23
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:37,960
yesterday's level.

24
00:00:37,960 --> 00:00:40,560
That was already pretty insane.

25
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:42,360
Insane? There's still elite
and hardcore above that.

26
00:00:42,360 --> 00:00:43,360
So we can push him further.

27
00:00:43,360 --> 00:00:44,760
(Activating hard mode)
Turn up the heat.

28
00:00:44,760 --> 00:00:46,720
Next episode, I'm not solving a thing.

29
00:00:46,720 --> 00:00:48,160
(Truth Supply Station challenge:)
The Truth Supply Station

30
00:00:48,170 --> 00:00:48,960
(Collect fragments to get Skill Cards)
has prepared challenges

31
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:51,680
to help everyone level up.

32
00:00:52,280 --> 00:00:54,640
(Really feeling himself)
♪You got me drunk♪

33
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:57,080
(Rainy-day karaoke)
♪Let all this rain come pouring down♪

34
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:58,040
Oh, oh, oh.

35
00:00:58,040 --> 00:00:59,720
What's that "oh, oh, oh"?

36
00:00:59,720 --> 00:01:01,000
(Testing his luck)
Mm-hmm-hmm.

37
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:03,940
(Checking the vibe)

38
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:04,680
Go bigger.

39
00:01:04,680 --> 00:01:05,560
(Stirring the pot)
Bigger.

40
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:06,920
Bigger.

41
00:01:10,540 --> 00:01:12,820
=Truth Supply Station=

42
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:15,440
Come on, guys. Grab a seat.

43
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:17,280
(Teasing)
When's your concert?

44
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:19,400
(Ning thinks back)
This year.

45
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:22,040
I have one more in April,
then that's it.

46
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:22,880
Where?

47
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:24,040
Nanjing.

48
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:26,040
Your hair.

49
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,080
(Secret spotted)
Your hair

50
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:28,360
has that "gets greasier every day" vibe.

51
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:30,160
Yeah. That's exactly it.

52
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:31,560
No, seriously.

53
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:32,040
It's so true.

54
00:01:32,040 --> 00:01:33,360
Day one, fluffy.

55
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:34,640
Day two...

56
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:35,080
Greasy.

57
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:35,800
A little shine up top.

58
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:37,120
Day three, it just lies flat.

59
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,200
My hair's already stiff as a board.

60
00:01:40,340 --> 00:01:41,420
(Hair evolution)

61
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:43,240
(Wen sees everything)
It's clearly hair gel.

62
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:45,640
Big shoot tomorrow?

63
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,300
(Ke is curious)

64
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:46,960
Shoot?

65
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:48,600
Call time probably won't be that early.

66
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:51,040
But we'll shoot till sunrise.

67
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:54,120
I'll stand in for you.

68
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:54,640
Then later,

69
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,520
(I'll run the scene)
they can CGI your face in later.

70
00:01:55,520 --> 00:01:56,240
Can they?

71
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:57,600
(Ke volunteers too)
Both of us can.

72
00:01:58,120 --> 00:01:58,960
(Gladly accepts)
Sure. Works for me.

73
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:00,140
You have my permission.

74
00:02:00,140 --> 00:02:01,060
(Officially authorized)

75
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:02,300
(That's our He)

76
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:06,040
Welcome to Truth Supply Station.

77
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:07,760
Here are the rules.

78
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:10,080
(Truth Supply Station:)
During every investigation,

79
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:11,960
you'll find stamina markers.

80
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:14,160
The ones you're always rushing to tap?

81
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:14,760
Exactly.

82
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:16,280
Once you find one,

83
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:17,120
use your

84
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,360
stamina badge

85
00:02:18,420 --> 00:02:18,960
(Stamina badge)

86
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:20,120
to tap it right away.

87
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,920
Each successful tap

88
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:23,400
earns you 100 points.

89
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:24,560
But each marker

90
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:25,600
can only be used once.

91
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:27,200
You can spend your stamina points

92
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:29,160
right here at Truth Supply Station

93
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:31,560
(Use stamina points for food and supplies)
for food and supplies.

94
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,960
Everyone starts

95
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:33,700
with 100 points.

96
00:02:33,780 --> 00:02:36,020
(Starting stamina:
100 points each)

97
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:37,040
Now let's check

98
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:38,760
the players' current stamina points.

99
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:40,640
Ding Chengxin has 600 points.

100
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:41,720
(Ding Chengxin: 600 stamina points)
How do I have that many?

101
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:42,960
(Ding searches every corner)
They're getting divorced anyway.

102
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:44,040
No one's sleeping on this bed.

103
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:45,000
Flip it into your room.

104
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:45,560
Sibling.

105
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:49,560
(Stamina marker found)
There it is again. The meal-card thing.

106
00:02:51,020 --> 00:02:51,780
(Ding Chengxin +100 stamina points)

107
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,080
I don't even know what to say.

108
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:54,600
(Ding is observing)
Nobody told me about this.

109
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:56,160
You're drunk too?

110
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:58,400
Wait.

111
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,320
This one's already tapped.

112
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:00,560
No, it isn't.

113
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:01,280
When did you tap it?

114
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:01,800
I didn't.

115
00:03:02,060 --> 00:03:03,580
(Ding Chengxin +100 stamina points)

116
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:06,220
(Ding Chengxin +100 stamina points)

117
00:03:07,460 --> 00:03:08,380
(Ding Chengxin +100 stamina points)

118
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:09,820
(Ding Chengxin +100 stamina points)

119
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:11,020
(Ding Chengxin: 600 stamina points,
including starting points)

120
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,160
That many?

121
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:12,580
(Jealous)

122
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:14,360
How did you quietly get all those?

123
00:03:14,420 --> 00:03:16,220
(Quietly powerful)

124
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:16,900
Second place.

125
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:18,640
(That's me)
That must be Liu Yuning, right?

126
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:19,400
Wait.

127
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,600
(Ning to win. No surrender)

128
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:20,960
Guys.

129
00:03:23,460 --> 00:03:24,740
(I'll take that)

130
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:26,820
(Liu Yuning +100 stamina points)

131
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,280
Seriously? Still thinking about food?

132
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:30,200
At a time like this,
you're still thinking about food?

133
00:03:32,060 --> 00:03:32,700
(He found something)

134
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:34,080
What's this?

135
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:36,120
Hurry.

136
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:37,720
I want to eat.

137
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:38,680
I'm your big bro.

138
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:39,560
Please let me have it.

139
00:03:40,380 --> 00:03:41,480
(Beat him to it)
Done.

140
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:42,180
(Liu Yuning scan successful)
I want to eat.

141
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:43,580
(Liu Yuning +100 stamina points)

142
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:44,580
Ding.

143
00:03:44,580 --> 00:03:45,440
(A rival appears)
Ding,

144
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:46,140
find the stamina markers.

145
00:03:46,140 --> 00:03:47,580
(Your Ding has entered the battlefield)

146
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:48,700
(Anticipating)

147
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:49,640
(First to strike)
Found one.

148
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:50,860
Ding!

149
00:03:50,860 --> 00:03:51,380
(Panicking)

150
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:53,640
(This is killing me)
He's going to steal it!

151
00:03:54,220 --> 00:03:55,260
(Liu Yuning +100 stamina points)

152
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,120
(Found another one)
Is that a stamina marker?

153
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,400
Ding, quick!

154
00:03:58,540 --> 00:03:59,420
(Must win this)

155
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:02,700
(Here he comes again)
Ding!

156
00:04:02,780 --> 00:04:04,700
(Too fast)

157
00:04:04,780 --> 00:04:06,460
(Liu Yuning +100 stamina points)

158
00:04:06,460 --> 00:04:07,260
(Late again)

159
00:04:07,260 --> 00:04:08,380
(Liu Yuning: 500 stamina points,
including starting points)

160
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,720
(No comeback now)
Even calling me won't help.

161
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,640
Liu Yuning's the type

162
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:12,160
to spot it first,

163
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:13,520
then go,

164
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:14,480
(Time to imitate him)
"Okay, let's talk this through".

165
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:15,480
Halfway through,

166
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:16,640
he'd sneak back and tap it.

167
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:19,320
You little food gremlin.

168
00:04:19,860 --> 00:04:21,780
(Thanks for the win)

169
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,760
Next episode, I'm not solving anything.

170
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:25,120
I'm just hunting these down.

171
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:27,100
(Here for the chaos)

172
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,600
Jin Jing, Zhang Linghe, and Zhou Keyu

173
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,520
each have 100 starting points.

174
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,180
(Starting stamina: 100 points)

175
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:32,640
As for Wen, she's...

176
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,120
- a limited-time player.
- Limited-time player.

177
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:35,420
(No stamina badge for limited-time players)
So she doesn't get points.

178
00:04:35,540 --> 00:04:37,260
(Then how?)

179
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:41,480
Will you buy me dinner?

180
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:42,920
Sure. No problem.

181
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:44,140
(That quick?)

182
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:45,800
Everyone else did great too,

183
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:46,520
(Wen gives her Golden Key to Jin)
but I think

184
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:48,360
my top pick

185
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,520
has to be Jin.

186
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:50,440
Give it to her for me.

187
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:52,980
An Xiaowen, thank you.

188
00:04:53,140 --> 00:04:54,740
(Thanks for dinner)

189
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:56,400
Jin Jing, let me paint you a picture.

190
00:04:56,660 --> 00:04:58,020
(What now?)

191
00:04:58,320 --> 00:04:58,960
At the end,

192
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:01,280
when we wrap the season
and count everything,

193
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,640
you only have two Golden Keys,

194
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:04,440
and one of them is from Wen.

195
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,160
Ning, listen.

196
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,680
All the female guests coming later

197
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:12,600
are my friends.

198
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,320
I may have to count on them

199
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:15,680
(Winning by being gifted)
giving me Golden Keys.

200
00:05:16,860 --> 00:05:18,220
(That's my girl)

201
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:20,320
Okay, so at the finale,

202
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,040
they'll say, "Congrats, Jin Jing.

203
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:22,960
You won first place this season.

204
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:23,680
But all your Golden Keys

205
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,600
(We can already see it)
came from the guest stars".

206
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,600
Wouldn't that crush you?

207
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:27,160
Nope.

208
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:27,680
Then what was all this filming for?

209
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:28,560
(You're overthinking it)
Nope.

210
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,040
You won't?

211
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:29,960
She'd love that even more.

212
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:31,000
I think she'd love it more.

213
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,520
(They know you too well)
I think she'd love it more too.

214
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:33,920
Yeah, she'd love it more.

215
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:35,240
Surviving on handouts.

216
00:05:35,540 --> 00:05:37,380
(Crowdfunded Key Queen)

217
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,280
Can we order first?

218
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:40,960
Sure.

219
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:42,070
(Ordering time)
Okay.

220
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:43,480
Let's check the menu.

221
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:43,760
Here.

222
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:47,160
(Today's menu)
First, the Truth Lunch Box.

223
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,040
100 stamina points.

224
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:49,420
A lunch box? Who wants that?

225
00:05:49,420 --> 00:05:50,340
(We deserve better)

226
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:53,640
Truth Flavor Set, 300 stamina points.

227
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:56,040
Truth Spicy Set, 300 stamina points.

228
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:57,360
That's the spicy one.

229
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:59,680
Truth Fresh Set, 300 stamina points.

230
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:00,880
Why is it so pricey?

231
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,210
(Are these prices real?)
300 stamina points each?

232
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:04,120
Pricey? You didn't even work
for those points.

233
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:05,360
You got them for free.

234
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:06,720
It's a perk.

235
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:07,480
And you're complaining?

236
00:06:07,820 --> 00:06:09,900
(Food gremlin)
Right. Fair.

237
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:10,960
Let me ask you something.

238
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:11,960
If you get those sets,

239
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:14,440
you wouldn't keep them all, right?

240
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:20,480
(Of course he wouldn't)
Ning wouldn't do us like that.

241
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,120
Of course I wouldn't.

242
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:24,720
What am I to you guys? Good big bro.

243
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:25,140
Our dad.

244
00:06:25,140 --> 00:06:26,340
(Door of Truth's best big bro)

245
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:30,760
How about this?

246
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:32,080
Let's order one set first.

247
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:32,880
See how much food it is.

248
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:33,680
Just one.

249
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,040
Try one set first.

250
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,400
If it's enough for everyone,

251
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,640
we don't spend more, right?

252
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:39,080
That's smart.

253
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:40,140
(Agreed)

254
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:41,120
Makes sense.

255
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:43,480
So we spend their points first, right?

256
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:44,960
I say we start

257
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:46,000
(I have a plan)
with Ning.

258
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,520
(Great minds think alike)
If he doesn't pay first, how can we?

259
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:49,630
(Exactly)
Right.

260
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,640
In the Northeast,
that's embarrassing a man.

261
00:06:54,020 --> 00:06:55,460
(Watching the drama)

262
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,800
Then let's do this.

263
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:59,480
To prove the three of you
are sincere, here.

264
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:01,840
You three pool your points for one set.

265
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,320
(That plan is way too obvious)
We can't pool them, Ning.

266
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,100
(Tiny rage)

267
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:05,960
No, wait.

268
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:06,640
I remember.

269
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:08,300
When Ning tapped his card, he said,

270
00:07:08,380 --> 00:07:09,740
(What did he say?)

271
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:11,240
"Even if I don't eat later,

272
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:13,080
I want bargaining power".

273
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,440
That's fine. I'll mooch off him.

274
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:15,160
You can mooch off me.

275
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:16,280
But once I have this,

276
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:17,600
I get bargaining power.

277
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:19,160
So his bargaining power

278
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:20,300
is making you three split it.

279
00:07:20,300 --> 00:07:21,020
(Now it makes sense)

280
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,240
No, wait.

281
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,160
This big bro is slick.

282
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:26,320
Wait, we have a new big bro.

283
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:29,920
New?

284
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,280
Me? Big Bro "Xin"?

285
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:32,800
(Big Bro Xin)
Right. Big Bro No. 2.

286
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,480
Big Bro No. 2.

287
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:35,840
Think back.

288
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:36,920
Every time it got dark,

289
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:38,160
who was by your side?

290
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:38,720
Exactly.

291
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:41,040
How about we meet in the middle?

292
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,720
Each side orders one set.

293
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:44,000
Okay.

294
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:44,640
That works.

295
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,280
(You buy one set)
You get one. He gets one.

296
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:47,360
(The three of us buy one)
We get one.

297
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,000
Right.

298
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,240
What do you want?

299
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,800
(Treat ourselves)
Let's get barbecue.

300
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:52,880
(Order: Truth Fired-Up Set, 300 stamina points)
Okay, Truth Fired-Up Set.

301
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:53,840
Tap your card.

302
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:54,600
Go tap it.

303
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:56,680
(Pooling points for food)
We'll each tap in.

304
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:02,460
(Food incoming)

305
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:04,280
This set is huge.

306
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,080
(The feast is here)
Guys.

307
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:08,920
Want help carrying it?

308
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,360
No need.

309
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,760
I'll feed you myself.

310
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,360
It's actually a lot of food.

311
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:15,360
Next time we're hungry,

312
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:17,440
(Budgeting like pros)
300 points can feed all of us.

313
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:17,760
Right?

314
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,360
So good.

315
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:20,680
We just need a main dish.

316
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:21,920
Let's order one more.

317
00:08:22,220 --> 00:08:22,620
(Sounds good)

318
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:23,240
I'll get one.

319
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:23,940
What do you want?

320
00:08:23,940 --> 00:08:24,660
(Generous)

321
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:26,160
Let's get Truth Flavor Set.

322
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:27,720
(Order: Truth Flavor Set, 300 stamina points)
Okay, Truth Flavor Set it is.

323
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:29,320
So good.

324
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:32,080
Done.

325
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,600
It should be that set.

326
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,910
Like a proper meal.

327
00:08:36,910 --> 00:08:37,520
Okay.

328
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:38,520
Enough to eat?

329
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:39,480
Yeah, enough.

330
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,900
(Smart spending, no waste)
I think it's enough.

331
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,760
(Ding buys drinks)
What drinks do you want?

332
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,220
(Then I'll take one. Soda +1)
I want soda.

333
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:45,840
(Soda +2)
Soda for me too.

334
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,120
(Soda +3)
Soda.

335
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,200
(Water +2)
Water.

336
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,760
(Water +3)
Me too. Water.

337
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:51,880
Three sodas, three waters.

338
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:54,880
(Dungeon One,
Supply Station stamina spent)

339
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:55,360
(Truth Fired-Up Set: 300 stamina points)

340
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:55,780
(Truth Flavor Set: 300 stamina points)

341
00:08:55,780 --> 00:08:56,180
(Water: 150 stamina points,
Soda: 150 stamina points)

342
00:08:56,180 --> 00:08:56,660
(Dungeon One,
Player stamina balance)

343
00:08:56,660 --> 00:08:57,290
(Liu Yuning: 200, Jin Jing: 0,
Zhang Linghe: 0)

344
00:08:57,290 --> 00:08:57,780
(Ding Chengxin: 300, Zhou Keyu: 0)

345
00:09:03,940 --> 00:09:05,310
(Thoughtful water service)
Soda.

346
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:07,200
We can't let Big Bro Xin serve us.

347
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:08,440
(Thoughtful Big Bro Xin)
Thanks, Big Bro Xin.

348
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,360
Thanks, Big Bro Xin.

349
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:12,080
(Ke-style feeding)
Ding, want some century egg congee?

350
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:13,600
Sure. Sounds good.

351
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:14,520
I'll get it.

352
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,280
I'll scoop you some.

353
00:09:21,340 --> 00:09:22,860
(Savoring it)

354
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:32,180
(Digging in)

355
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:34,240
How's it been hanging out
with us these past few days?

356
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,720
How do we seem to you?

357
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:39,500
(Waiting)

358
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:40,480
I think you're all

359
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:41,880
really good people.

360
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:44,100
Yeah. I've had a lot of fun.

361
00:09:44,260 --> 00:09:45,780
(That's what matters)

362
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,800
Sometimes you guys are really cool.

363
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:49,280
(Tell us more)
Who was cool?

364
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,200
All of you.

365
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:54,840
(Impressed)
Watching you connect the clues

366
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,760
and figure out how the killer did it

367
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:57,240
was really cool.

368
00:09:58,480 --> 00:09:59,640
Like Ke,

369
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:01,640
he looked so cool backing me up. Right?

370
00:10:02,740 --> 00:10:03,820
(Brothers for life)

371
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:05,760
Wen, how was your first time here?

372
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:07,040
(Praise time)
Wen did great.

373
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:07,840
Day one,

374
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:08,720
I was doing okay.

375
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:10,160
I was getting into it.

376
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:11,720
By day two, I was done.

377
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:13,900
(Alive, but barely)

378
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,120
Then by day three,

379
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:16,320
I slowly started

380
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:18,040
getting the clues

381
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:18,960
(Making progress)
and the logic.

382
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,840
Day one was okay.

383
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:22,040
It was just flashing lights.

384
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:22,920
Right.

385
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:23,800
Then day two...

386
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,600
- Pitch black
- Yeah, lights out.

387
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,200
inside a tunnel.

388
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,320
With people hiding in there.

389
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:29,440
By the end, I was just in survival mode.

390
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:30,320
(Still scared)
You know?

391
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:32,280
People would actually jump out
and grab you.

392
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:33,960
Now even flickering lights scare me.

393
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,400
Ding and I
were practically breakdancing.

394
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,560
It felt like something could pop out
any second.

395
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:42,040
Ding, which is worse?

396
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:42,960
The lights go out.

397
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:43,960
There are six people in the room.

398
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:44,920
When the lights come back on,

399
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:45,680
would you rather find one extra person

400
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:46,760
or one missing?

401
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:48,180
No people. That's the scariest.

402
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:48,900
(More is fine. Less is not.)

403
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,680
I'd rather have one extra person.

404
00:10:53,460 --> 00:10:54,410
That reminds me

405
00:10:54,410 --> 00:10:55,920
of that traditional-style horror case.

406
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:57,340
That one was scary.

407
00:10:57,340 --> 00:10:59,140
(Still traumatized)
Even I thought it was terrifying.

408
00:10:59,140 --> 00:11:01,690
(New idea unlocked)
I say we give Ding one of those.

409
00:11:01,690 --> 00:11:03,780
(Ke agrees)
Ding needs a solo mission.

410
00:11:03,780 --> 00:11:05,380
(He agrees)
It doesn't even have to be horror.

411
00:11:05,380 --> 00:11:06,840
A solo mission is enough.

412
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:07,330
No, I just...

413
00:11:07,330 --> 00:11:08,020
I want to ask.

414
00:11:08,020 --> 00:11:10,840
Could you survive a solo mission?

415
00:11:12,050 --> 00:11:13,210
(Tough tone, soft answer)
Absolutely not.

416
00:11:16,150 --> 00:11:18,980
Ding, what's the craziest mission
you'd be willing to do?

417
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:20,850
Like, what's your nightmare difficulty?

418
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:23,280
Probably yesterday's level.

419
00:11:23,860 --> 00:11:25,090
That's your max?

420
00:11:25,550 --> 00:11:26,390
Not my limit exactly.

421
00:11:26,390 --> 00:11:29,180
That was already pretty insane.

422
00:11:29,180 --> 00:11:29,580
Insane?

423
00:11:29,580 --> 00:11:31,020
There's still elite
and hardcore above that.

424
00:11:31,020 --> 00:11:32,040
So we can push him further.

425
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,970
(Activating hard mode)
Turn up the heat.

426
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,400
Have you done solo missions?

427
00:11:36,290 --> 00:11:36,880
Yeah.

428
00:11:37,410 --> 00:11:39,420
We had one set in a bunch of bathrooms.

429
00:11:40,910 --> 00:11:41,410
Right.

430
00:11:41,810 --> 00:11:42,980
One room.

431
00:11:42,980 --> 00:11:43,700
Different bathrooms.

432
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:46,130
(The Truth S2, Ep. 6, Part 2)
And that spinning disc.

433
00:11:46,130 --> 00:11:47,430
Everyone had to go in.

434
00:11:47,430 --> 00:11:48,510
(Scared senseless)
It was so scary.

435
00:11:48,950 --> 00:11:51,120
But you guys had partners that time.

436
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,620
You went in pairs.

437
00:11:52,620 --> 00:11:53,710
Only he was alone.

438
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,280
I was the only one alone.

439
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:56,130
I was alone too.

440
00:11:56,130 --> 00:11:57,390
I didn't have anyone either.

441
00:11:57,910 --> 00:11:59,110
It was one, two, and three.

442
00:11:59,110 --> 00:11:59,740
No.

443
00:11:59,740 --> 00:12:02,060
Who was with Dilraba back then?

444
00:12:02,340 --> 00:12:03,860
Dilraba, He, and I were together.

445
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:05,170
He was with Bai.

446
00:12:05,170 --> 00:12:06,210
You were alone.

447
00:12:06,210 --> 00:12:08,150
(Jin has a complaint)
Being with Bai was the scariest part.

448
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,140
He ran off right away.

449
00:12:10,140 --> 00:12:11,140
(Cracked up)

450
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:12,230
Where was Dilraba?

451
00:12:12,550 --> 00:12:14,030
Dilraba was alone.

452
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:14,900
No.

453
00:12:15,540 --> 00:12:16,420
Dilraba and I were together.

454
00:12:16,820 --> 00:12:17,380
(It clicks)

455
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:17,940
Right.

456
00:12:18,270 --> 00:12:18,960
Did you guys have

457
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:19,910
those moments

458
00:12:19,910 --> 00:12:23,300
where a hand suddenly reaches out
and grabs you?

459
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:24,870
That was really scary.

460
00:12:24,870 --> 00:12:26,590
Before that,

461
00:12:26,590 --> 00:12:27,230
I always thought

462
00:12:27,230 --> 00:12:29,500
(Still shaken)
NPCs weren't allowed to touch us.

463
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:31,340
Yeah, he got hit with a surprise hook.

464
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:33,770
When I went in,

465
00:12:33,770 --> 00:12:35,270
hands started coming out of the wall.

466
00:12:35,270 --> 00:12:36,700
They were actually grabbing me.

467
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:39,060
(Self-defense mode activated)
I just panicked and reacted.

468
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:40,170
They'd touch you like this.

469
00:12:40,170 --> 00:12:40,930
They actually touch you.

470
00:12:40,930 --> 00:12:42,510
That one really scared me.

471
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:44,000
Ding, do you regret coming?

472
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,240
No.

473
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:46,760
(Sweet talk mode)
How could I, with all of you here?

474
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:49,080
His EQ kicked in right away.

475
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:50,400
Let's do this.

476
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,120
Next time the lights go out,
we'll ask him again.

477
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:56,720
The Truth Supply Station

478
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,200
has prepared challenges

479
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,960
to help everyone level up.

480
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:02,000
First up, a challenge for observation,

481
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:02,960
judgment,

482
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:05,160
acting, and defense.

483
00:13:05,560 --> 00:13:06,840
Find the White Larks.

484
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:08,160
(Find the White Larks)
Among the six players,

485
00:13:08,160 --> 00:13:10,880
(Find the White Larks)
four Larks know the exact song prompt.

486
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:14,200
Two White Larks only get a vague prompt.

487
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:16,160
The White Larks don't know each other.

488
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:18,800
Find both White Larks
within three rounds,

489
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:20,520
and the Larks win.

490
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:23,320
If even one White Lark survives,

491
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:25,680
the White Larks win.

492
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:26,800
The winning team

493
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:28,840
gets one Skill Card fragment each.

494
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:29,960
Collect two fragments

495
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:31,400
to redeem a Skill Card.

496
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:32,480
Okay. Let's do it.

497
00:13:33,060 --> 00:13:34,620
(Find the White Larks: Round 1)

498
00:13:34,620 --> 00:13:36,740
(White Larks:
Use a song to describe XXX)

499
00:13:36,740 --> 00:13:38,620
(Larks:
Use a song to describe Zhang Linghe)

500
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:40,340
(Lark, White Lark)

501
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:42,000
Who starts?

502
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:42,640
(Singing order: Jin Jing first)
Let's do this.

503
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:43,480
Okay.

504
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:43,800
Works.

505
00:13:43,940 --> 00:13:45,100
(Lark prompt:
Use a song to describe Zhang Linghe)

506
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:46,770
(White Lark prompt:
Use a song to describe XXX)

507
00:13:46,770 --> 00:13:47,660
(White Lark)

508
00:13:47,680 --> 00:13:48,440
This is hard.

509
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:50,000
I barely know any songs.

510
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:51,280
Stop acting.

511
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,760
(Taking a jab)
Did you get the vague one?

512
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:55,400
(Adding fuel)
That sounds suspicious already.

513
00:13:56,980 --> 00:13:58,540
(Stirring the pot)

514
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:02,200
♪I want to sing for you♪

515
00:14:02,620 --> 00:14:05,540
(Trying to figure it out)

516
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,120
♪A big tree♪

517
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:11,080
♪A green blessing♪

518
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:17,120
Question me again, and I'll bite you.

519
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,000
Try it.

520
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,800
Are you actually going to bite me?

521
00:14:20,460 --> 00:14:22,620
(Sneaking a look)

522
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:26,160
♪Give me a drink to forget♪

523
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:28,820
(Got it)

524
00:14:29,340 --> 00:14:30,460
(No clue)

525
00:14:30,920 --> 00:14:31,480
Next.

526
00:14:34,560 --> 00:14:36,940
♪Let all this rain come pouring down♪

527
00:14:36,940 --> 00:14:37,780
(I'll go with a love song too)

528
00:14:44,420 --> 00:14:47,860
(Trying to stay calm)

529
00:14:47,940 --> 00:14:49,860
(That reaction...)

530
00:14:50,420 --> 00:14:51,260
(Time to act too)

531
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:52,880
So? What is it?

532
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:54,000
Your turn.

533
00:14:57,120 --> 00:15:00,560
♪I want to sing for you♪

534
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:03,720
♪Give me a drink to forget♪

535
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:06,100
(Love songs?)

536
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:09,360
♪I'd do it all for you♪

537
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:12,520
♪I'd do it all for you♪

538
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,000
Okay. Got it.

539
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:17,000
Everyone's so random.

540
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,600
♪His lashes, the curve of his smile♪

541
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:23,280
Okay. Got it.

542
00:15:23,660 --> 00:15:25,700
(Why the sudden genre switch?)

543
00:15:25,780 --> 00:15:27,260
(Singing ends)

544
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:29,040
This round, the Larks' prompt

545
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:31,260
was use a song to describe Zhang Linghe.

546
00:15:31,260 --> 00:15:33,100
(Me?)

547
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:34,320
The White Larks' prompt

548
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:36,720
was use a song to describe someone.

549
00:15:37,620 --> 00:15:38,500
(Acting mode on)

550
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:39,560
No way.

551
00:15:40,180 --> 00:15:42,780
(So that's it)

552
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:44,440
That's pretty close, though.

553
00:15:44,440 --> 00:15:46,640
Either way, you're singing to someone.

554
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:48,680
(Small jab)
Your song works for anyone.

555
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:50,320
Wait.

556
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,160
"His lashes"?

557
00:15:51,160 --> 00:15:52,920
You two explain yourselves first.

558
00:15:54,220 --> 00:15:55,660
(Watching the drama)

559
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:57,080
His song

560
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:57,800
was weird too.

561
00:15:58,140 --> 00:15:58,740
(Suddenly called out)

562
00:15:58,760 --> 00:15:59,620
No, actually, I...

563
00:15:59,620 --> 00:16:00,900
(Trying to defend himself)

564
00:16:00,980 --> 00:16:02,900
(Waiting for an explanation)

565
00:16:02,980 --> 00:16:05,340
(Brain, start working)

566
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:06,840
I don't even know.

567
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,640
(Please explain)
What am I in your hearts?

568
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:10,280
We'll explain later.

569
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:10,840
What's the rush?

570
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:11,880
Yeah, we'll explain.

571
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:12,400
We'll explain.

572
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:13,020
(Quickly playing along)

573
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:14,720
What about you?

574
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:16,280
♪I want to sing for you♪

575
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:17,200
Why?

576
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:18,840
Because he sang it recently,

577
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:20,120
and it was really good.

578
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:22,180
(Confirmed by the man himself)
Yes.

579
00:16:22,180 --> 00:16:30,420
(Footage sourced from the internet)

580
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:32,160
Okay, you're safe.

581
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:33,680
Why did you sing that one?

582
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:35,760
The prompt said
to describe Zhang Linghe.

583
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:37,560
So I went with his looks.

584
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:39,200
So you focused on "describe",

585
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,160
(Sharp)
not "Zhang Linghe".

586
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:41,080
That's suspicious.

587
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:41,240
Because...

588
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:41,600
No.

589
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,760
Not everyone has long lashes.

590
00:16:44,280 --> 00:16:45,680
(Caught him)
Who here has short lashes?

591
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:46,480
Go on. Say it.

592
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:49,000
(Quick save)
Mine aren't that long.

593
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:49,640
Okay?

594
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:52,000
Ning?

595
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:53,520
"A big tree".

596
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:55,600
I meant he's tall.

597
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:56,440
He's really tall.

598
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:57,720
If it were you,

599
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:59,840
I wouldn't sing "A big tree", right?

600
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:00,160
Fair.

601
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:00,840
If he were a White Lark,

602
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:02,360
he wouldn't pick such a vague song.

603
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:03,280
(Agreed)
That vague of a song.

604
00:17:03,280 --> 00:17:03,760
Right.

605
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:06,200
What did you sing?

606
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:08,480
♪Give me a drink to forget♪

607
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:09,280
Why?

608
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:10,680
Why?

609
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:11,100
(Instant follow-up)

610
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:12,110
Zhang.

611
00:17:13,590 --> 00:17:14,160
Zhang Xueyou.

612
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:14,640
Right.

613
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:16,070
That's Liu Dehua.

614
00:17:16,070 --> 00:17:16,920
Liu Dehua's song.

615
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:18,980
(He didn't mean to)

616
00:17:19,740 --> 00:17:20,540
(Didn't mean to laugh)

617
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:21,040
No.

618
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:22,400
(Winning over the good guys)
I think his logic checks out.

619
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:24,680
(Sorry)
I remembered wrong.

620
00:17:25,070 --> 00:17:26,350
Then over there...

621
00:17:26,350 --> 00:17:28,110
♪So you won't see my struggle♪

622
00:17:28,110 --> 00:17:29,360
Because he's the detective today.

623
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,280
I'm the killer.

624
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:38,380
(Still steering the vote)
I think I know who it is.

625
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:39,520
Go ahead. Vote.

626
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:40,480
Okay.

627
00:17:44,780 --> 00:17:47,380
(Round 1 votes:
Zhou Keyu, Wang Yuwen, Zhang Linghe)

628
00:17:47,820 --> 00:17:48,820
(Zhou Keyu eliminated with 3 votes)

629
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:51,960
Zhou Keyu, please reveal your role.

630
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,200
(White Lark: Zhou Keyu eliminated)

631
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:54,160
My friends,

632
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:58,400
I'm a White Lark.

633
00:17:58,500 --> 00:17:59,740
(Wrong, but confident)

634
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:06,220
White Lark?

635
00:18:06,220 --> 00:18:07,420
(Playing dumb)

636
00:18:07,580 --> 00:18:08,980
(Find the White Larks: Round 2)

637
00:18:16,620 --> 00:18:17,360
(Leading the order)
Let's do this.

638
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:17,760
Same as before.

639
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:18,400
Same order.

640
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:19,660
(Singing order)

641
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:20,800
My song is...

642
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:22,960
♪Why am I so pretty?♪

643
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:25,220
♪What do I do with all this beauty?♪

644
00:18:25,220 --> 00:18:26,020
(Lark prompt: You wake up as Jin Jing)

645
00:18:26,020 --> 00:18:27,220
(Looking in the mirror,
you want to sing...)

646
00:18:27,220 --> 00:18:27,700
(White Lark prompt: You wake up, look in the mirror,
and want to sing...)

647
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:29,740
(Enjoying the drama)

648
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:31,280
Pass.

649
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:34,720
Your face says everything.

650
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:36,960
Your turn.

651
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:43,560
♪This person is Mom♪

652
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:47,880
♪This person is Mother♪

653
00:18:52,620 --> 00:18:54,860
(Mom?)

654
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:58,760
♪Friends for life♪

655
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:02,120
(From mom to friend?)
♪Those days are gone♪

656
00:19:03,520 --> 00:19:04,840
Your turn.

657
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:07,120
My angle is so weird.

658
00:19:07,120 --> 00:19:07,480
Why?

659
00:19:09,360 --> 00:19:11,920
♪My baby♪

660
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:13,640
♪A little sweetness for you♪

661
00:19:13,640 --> 00:19:16,640
♪Sleep well tonight♪

662
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:18,920
This?

663
00:19:20,340 --> 00:19:22,300
(From friend to baby?)

664
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:24,760
I can explain later.

665
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:25,800
Okay.

666
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:26,400
Your turn.

667
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,240
Okay.

668
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:28,120
I'll sing.

669
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:31,800
I don't know that many songs.
Let me think.

670
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:33,480
This one's hard.

671
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:38,560
♪Ten years ago, I didn't know you♪

672
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:40,800
♪You weren't mine♪

673
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:42,720
♪We were still friends♪

674
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:45,880
This is tricky.

675
00:19:46,820 --> 00:19:48,740
(Panicking)

676
00:19:48,820 --> 00:19:50,060
(This is tricky)

677
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:51,400
Should we do another round?

678
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:52,900
Two prompts should be enough to tell.

679
00:19:53,180 --> 00:19:54,180
(Overtime)

680
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:55,360
Okay, I'll sing this.

681
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:59,280
♪A woman blooms in the world♪

682
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:02,760
♪Softly swaying with the wind♪

683
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:07,160
♪There was a girl♪

684
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,960
♪Bold and a little reckless♪

685
00:20:10,160 --> 00:20:11,720
♪That girl is me♪

686
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:15,160
That fits better, right?

687
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:16,200
(Brainstorming)
Okay.

688
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:18,080
♪You are♪

689
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:20,480
♪A pretty silly woman♪

690
00:20:22,380 --> 00:20:25,180
(Something about women?)

691
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:27,280
Your turn.

692
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:28,880
Let me think.

693
00:20:34,280 --> 00:20:36,040
You're taking the longest.

694
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:37,560
You're more suspicious
than Zhang Linghe now.

695
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:38,920
Mine is...

696
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:40,400
(Trying hard to clear himself)
How am I suddenly suspicious?

697
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:44,600
♪Ducks swim under the bridge♪

698
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:47,120
♪Come count them♪

699
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:48,440
♪Two, four, six, seven, eight♪

700
00:20:49,740 --> 00:20:51,300
(How did this become counting ducks?)

701
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:51,920
Very accurate.

702
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:53,720
He, go.

703
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:56,400
♪The sparrow outside♪

704
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:58,600
♪On the pole♪

705
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:01,200
♪Keeps chattering♪

706
00:21:01,340 --> 00:21:02,220
(Couldn't hold it in)

707
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:08,200
(Singing ends)
This round, the Larks

708
00:21:08,760 --> 00:21:09,760
were told that they wake up

709
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:11,360
and find you've become Jin Jing.

710
00:21:11,360 --> 00:21:14,040
Looking in the mirror,
you want to sing...

711
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:16,400
The White Larks' prompt

712
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:17,600
was you wake up,

713
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:20,120
look in the mirror, and want to sing...

714
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:23,280
Looking in the mirror?

715
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:24,220
When we see ourselves?

716
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:25,220
(Fishing for clues)

717
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:27,360
♪Why am I so pretty?♪

718
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:33,160
After hearing the undercover prompt,

719
00:21:33,160 --> 00:21:34,120
I feel so full of myself.

720
00:21:35,080 --> 00:21:37,120
I feel like your answers

721
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:37,680
are kind of random.

722
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:39,720
Right now, you two are weird.

723
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:41,680
Ding and Wen are both weird.

724
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,600
If Ding saw you in the mirror,

725
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:46,080
he wouldn't sing about ducks

726
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:47,040
under a bridge.

727
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:48,400
But if her prompt

728
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:49,800
was looking in the mirror and seeing me,

729
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:51,840
she would sing "Why Am I So Pretty?".

730
00:21:51,980 --> 00:21:54,060
(How did I become suspicious?)

731
00:21:54,580 --> 00:21:55,620
(Makes sense)

732
00:21:56,020 --> 00:21:56,860
(Successfully led everyone astray)

733
00:21:57,040 --> 00:21:57,500
Let's vote.

734
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:58,540
(Victory is mine)

735
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:00,360
You gave me your Golden Key.

736
00:22:00,380 --> 00:22:01,260
(Secretly switching sides)
I won't vote for you.

737
00:22:01,300 --> 00:22:02,340
(For the key, Wen gets a pass)

738
00:22:02,340 --> 00:22:03,740
(Round 2 voting)

739
00:22:03,740 --> 00:22:04,740
(Wang Yuwen, Jin Jing, Ding Chengxin)

740
00:22:04,740 --> 00:22:05,460
(Sacrificing herself for Wen)

741
00:22:05,860 --> 00:22:07,220
(Wang Yuwen still eliminated
with 3 votes)

742
00:22:07,660 --> 00:22:08,760
(Got away with it)
Did we win?

743
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:11,040
I'm a Lark.

744
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:12,460
(Fake shock)

745
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:15,080
I told you.

746
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:16,120
After hearing the White Lark prompt,

747
00:22:16,120 --> 00:22:17,000
I knew mine sounded ridiculous.

748
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,480
It made me sound so vain.

749
00:22:18,480 --> 00:22:19,880
But I really was thinking of you.

750
00:22:21,700 --> 00:22:23,740
(Then it has to be you)

751
00:22:24,980 --> 00:22:25,840
(It really isn't me)
It's not me.

752
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:27,980
(Survived another round)

753
00:22:27,980 --> 00:22:29,540
(Find the White Larks: Round 3)

754
00:22:29,540 --> 00:22:32,620
(Find the White Larks)

755
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:33,800
Let's do rock-paper-scissors.

756
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:34,520
Loser sings first.

757
00:22:35,120 --> 00:22:36,600
Rock, paper, scissors.

758
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:38,120
Okay.

759
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:40,020
Rock, paper, scissors.

760
00:22:40,060 --> 00:22:40,560
(Zhang Linghe goes first)

761
00:22:40,560 --> 00:22:41,040
I'll go first.

762
00:22:41,960 --> 00:22:43,140
(Uh-oh)
This one's hard.

763
00:22:43,140 --> 00:22:43,890
(Lark prompt: You're at your ex's wedding
and it hurts to watch)

764
00:22:43,890 --> 00:22:44,660
(You decide to crash it,
grab the mic, and sing)

765
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:46,160
This one should be easy.

766
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:46,700
No.

767
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:47,920
(White Lark prompt:
You're at someone's wedding)

768
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,340
(Everyone's happy, so you sing for them)

769
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:51,920
♪You got me drunk♪

770
00:22:52,040 --> 00:22:52,920
Oh, oh, oh.

771
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,840
What's that "oh, oh, oh"?

772
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:56,720
It's in the song.

773
00:22:57,520 --> 00:22:59,160
My song library is empty. What do I do?

774
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:04,720
Give me back what you owe me.

775
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:05,200
I want it...

776
00:23:06,040 --> 00:23:07,120
back.

777
00:23:08,480 --> 00:23:11,240
♪The one beside you♪

778
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:14,280
(Instant sing-along)
♪Has taken my place♪

779
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:15,640
Keep going.

780
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:16,220
(We need more)
I'm done.

781
00:23:16,220 --> 00:23:16,760
(Slightly disappointed)

782
00:23:16,760 --> 00:23:17,760
Okay.

783
00:23:17,760 --> 00:23:19,140
(So what is it?)

784
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:23,200
♪Do you love me or him?♪

785
00:23:24,120 --> 00:23:25,840
I can't understand
what they're singing at all.

786
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,300
Me neither.

787
00:23:27,300 --> 00:23:28,620
(Even better)

788
00:23:28,620 --> 00:23:29,720
(Singing ends)

789
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:31,280
The Larks' prompt

790
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:32,840
was you're at your ex's wedding.

791
00:23:32,840 --> 00:23:34,160
The longer you watch,
the worse it feels.

792
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:36,200
So you decide to steal them away.

793
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:38,600
You grab the mic and sing.

794
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:40,400
The White Larks' prompt

795
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:42,200
was you're at someone's wedding.

796
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:43,800
Everyone's in a great mood,

797
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:45,440
so you sing for them.

798
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:46,480
(Catching the key point)
Who sounded happy?

799
00:23:47,740 --> 00:23:48,700
(That would be me)

800
00:23:49,160 --> 00:23:50,000
Hers was...

801
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:50,690
(Led astray)
♪Mine♪

802
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:51,920
♪Give it back♪

803
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:53,200
I was taking it back.

804
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:55,240
I got it. I know who it is.

805
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:56,720
I got it too.

806
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:57,280
I know.

807
00:23:58,940 --> 00:24:00,220
(Am I done for?)

808
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:01,840
It's really not me.

809
00:24:02,680 --> 00:24:04,440
No one said it was you.

810
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:06,280
No one said it was you.

811
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:06,760
It's just...

812
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:08,840
First, I barely know any songs.

813
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:10,840
And the keyword I caught

814
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:12,440
was crashing the wedding.

815
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:14,960
Who crashes a wedding that happily?

816
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:15,620
(Instant call-out)

817
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:16,680
How was I supposed to know

818
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:18,120
that was a happy song?

819
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:19,360
Let's talk.

820
00:24:19,380 --> 00:24:20,040
(Teaming up with the enemy)

821
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:20,760
Who do you think it is?

822
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:22,400
(You call it, teammate)
You decide.

823
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:23,360
Let's vote Jin.

824
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:23,920
Number three.

825
00:24:24,300 --> 00:24:25,780
(Jin Jing eliminated with 3 votes)

826
00:24:25,780 --> 00:24:27,500
(Can't hide the smile)

827
00:24:27,820 --> 00:24:29,840
(Doubting herself)
I'm a Lark.

828
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:33,660
Sorry. I'm a White Lark.

829
00:24:33,700 --> 00:24:34,780
(No more pretending)

830
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:37,560
We...

831
00:24:37,840 --> 00:24:38,500
We...

832
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:39,020
(I blew it)

833
00:24:40,840 --> 00:24:42,600
You guys took yourselves out...

834
00:24:42,600 --> 00:24:44,000
(Ke backed by He)
Full-on friendly fire.

835
00:24:45,300 --> 00:24:47,180
(Regrets were had)

836
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:49,360
Why would you sing that

837
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:50,600
for a happy wedding?

838
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:52,200
Because I guessed

839
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:53,440
if mine was an acquaintance's wedding,

840
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:54,800
yours might be a stranger

841
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:55,760
or an enemy.

842
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:56,340
(Mastermind)

843
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:58,520
Genius. Actually genius.

844
00:24:59,140 --> 00:25:00,380
(Keeping it humble)

845
00:25:00,560 --> 00:25:02,000
Congratulations to the White Larks.

846
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,640
Each of you gets a fragment.

847
00:25:03,720 --> 00:25:04,560
I get one too?

848
00:25:04,560 --> 00:25:06,120
You two were both White Larks.

849
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:07,160
(Carried to victory)
Yep.

850
00:25:07,160 --> 00:25:07,720
Bro.

851
00:25:07,720 --> 00:25:08,360
Same team.

852
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:09,700
Easy win.

853
00:25:09,700 --> 00:25:10,540
(Jealous)

854
00:25:11,120 --> 00:25:12,360
A real easy win.

855
00:25:12,420 --> 00:25:14,260
(Carried this round)

856
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:15,440
Next up is a challenge

857
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:16,440
for your imagination.

858
00:25:16,620 --> 00:25:18,700
(The Yes-or-No Humming Challenge)

859
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:20,560
(The Yes-or-No Humming Challenge)
The blindfolded player

860
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:21,520
has five minutes to complete the task.

861
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:23,880
Everyone else can only hint

862
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:25,560
with yes or no hums.

863
00:25:25,560 --> 00:25:28,280
If at least three players succeed,

864
00:25:28,280 --> 00:25:29,640
they earn one fragment.

865
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:31,120
Got it.

866
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:32,440
Who's first?

867
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:34,180
(I'll show you)
I'll go first.

868
00:25:34,180 --> 00:25:35,100
(Round 1)

869
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:36,260
(Task: Take Liu Yuning's hand
and pat your own head)

870
00:25:36,280 --> 00:25:36,800
Okay. Go.

871
00:25:37,980 --> 00:25:39,460
(Dancing?)

872
00:25:43,340 --> 00:25:44,020
(Plate?)

873
00:25:48,620 --> 00:25:49,980
(Chair?)

874
00:25:57,100 --> 00:25:58,460
(Him)

875
00:26:13,260 --> 00:26:14,810
(Challenge complete)
Correct.

876
00:26:14,840 --> 00:26:15,840
I have no idea what we were doing.

877
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:17,280
He's so good at this.

878
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:18,680
Just keep moving.

879
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:19,820
(Pro tip)
Keep moving, and you'll get it.

880
00:26:19,940 --> 00:26:21,140
(Liu Yuning's challenge)

881
00:26:21,140 --> 00:26:22,220
(Round 2)

882
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:22,620
Okay.

883
00:26:22,620 --> 00:26:24,740
(Task: Give Zhang Linghe
a piggyback ride)

884
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:26,680
Let's move back a bit.

885
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:27,840
Give him some room.

886
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:28,680
Okay, go.

887
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:33,580
(This way)

888
00:26:36,380 --> 00:26:38,140
(Look at me)

889
00:26:38,860 --> 00:26:41,700
(Trying things out)

890
00:26:41,820 --> 00:26:44,060
(Nope)

891
00:26:46,740 --> 00:26:48,100
(Here)

892
00:26:53,220 --> 00:26:54,860
(Not me)

893
00:26:56,060 --> 00:26:57,660
(It's him)

894
00:26:58,900 --> 00:27:00,060
(No clue where to start)

895
00:27:00,500 --> 00:27:02,100
(So stressful to watch)

896
00:27:06,700 --> 00:27:07,580
(Sit?)

897
00:27:09,680 --> 00:27:10,380
Interact.

898
00:27:10,460 --> 00:27:11,260
(Move around)

899
00:27:11,500 --> 00:27:12,780
(So obedient)

900
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:15,240
Go bigger.

901
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:16,820
Bigger.

902
00:27:16,820 --> 00:27:17,380
(Use your imagination)

903
00:27:19,300 --> 00:27:19,820
(Big enough?)

904
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:21,160
Bigger.

905
00:27:24,800 --> 00:27:25,280
No.

906
00:27:27,100 --> 00:27:28,220
(Taking it off?)

907
00:27:31,540 --> 00:27:32,620
(Higher)

908
00:27:47,940 --> 00:27:48,800
(Fine, one more hint)
Turn around.

909
00:27:49,900 --> 00:27:51,380
(Standing straight)

910
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:51,960
What?

911
00:27:52,660 --> 00:27:53,460
(That's it)

912
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:55,040
Now what?

913
00:27:58,860 --> 00:28:00,220
(Hug?)

914
00:28:01,660 --> 00:28:03,940
(Give up)

915
00:28:07,300 --> 00:28:09,900
(Finally got it)

916
00:28:16,340 --> 00:28:17,740
(Challenge complete)

917
00:28:21,080 --> 00:28:21,640
It's over.

918
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:23,860
Wait, my abs hurt.

919
00:28:23,860 --> 00:28:24,460
(Went too hard)
I'm already...

920
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:26,360
You looked just like
that radish tissue cat meme.

921
00:28:28,540 --> 00:28:30,220
(Finally over)

922
00:28:32,700 --> 00:28:34,660
(Round 3)

923
00:28:35,140 --> 00:28:36,180
(Wen is ready)

924
00:28:36,180 --> 00:28:37,620
(Task: Runway walk, pose,
hand on hip, look back)

925
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:38,040
Okay.

926
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:38,760
Okay, go.

927
00:28:44,540 --> 00:28:45,300
(That way?)

928
00:28:48,740 --> 00:28:49,220
(Go out?)

929
00:28:57,460 --> 00:28:58,180
(This?)

930
00:28:58,820 --> 00:29:00,100
(Yes)

931
00:29:15,340 --> 00:29:17,460
(Almost)

932
00:29:22,140 --> 00:29:23,540
(Accidental hand on hip)

933
00:29:25,820 --> 00:29:27,020
(Exactly)

934
00:29:29,660 --> 00:29:30,540
(Hand on hip first?)

935
00:29:34,540 --> 00:29:35,500
(Hand on hip?)

936
00:29:43,260 --> 00:29:45,940
(Proud)

937
00:29:49,380 --> 00:29:51,380
(Getting close)

938
00:29:51,940 --> 00:29:52,620
(Spin?)

939
00:29:57,220 --> 00:29:58,260
(What is it?)

940
00:29:58,300 --> 00:29:59,380
(Another accidental look back)

941
00:29:59,460 --> 00:30:00,540
(Like this?)

942
00:30:00,980 --> 00:30:02,620
(Exactly)

943
00:30:04,060 --> 00:30:05,020
(That's it?)

944
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:05,960
What was it?

945
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:07,200
Look.

946
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:11,520
This one's hard.

947
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:12,240
But you did it.

948
00:30:12,240 --> 00:30:13,040
Great job.

949
00:30:13,360 --> 00:30:13,760
No, but...

950
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:14,480
Every time I did something,

951
00:30:14,480 --> 00:30:15,200
(Nod means yes)
someone went "mm-hmm",

952
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:15,800
(Shake means no)
and someone went "mm-mm".

953
00:30:16,780 --> 00:30:17,260
(Game over)

954
00:30:17,260 --> 00:30:18,100
(All three succeeded,
and each earned one fragment)

955
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:20,200
Congrats to Zhang Linghe and Zhou Keyu.

956
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:21,440
You've collected two fragments.

957
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:23,240
You can redeem a Skill Card.

958
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:24,200
Which card we've used before

959
00:30:24,200 --> 00:30:25,600
was the most useful?

960
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:26,160
I was thinking...

961
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:27,720
In this case,

962
00:30:27,720 --> 00:30:28,640
without the Restore Card,

963
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:30,720
could we have solved it?

964
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:31,120
Today,

965
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:32,640
if we hadn't restored the glass,

966
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:33,560
would we have figured it out?

967
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:35,040
No.

968
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:37,120
We wouldn't even know the box had...

969
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:38,540
(Zhou Keyu redeems a Restore Card)
Then I'll take Restore Card.

970
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:39,900
(Zhang Linghe redeems a Copy Card)
I'll take Copy Card.

971
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:43,160
That's a wrap on Truth Supply Station.

972
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:43,760
Great.

973
00:30:43,760 --> 00:30:45,680
Please head to the next dungeon.

974
00:30:45,680 --> 00:30:46,520
Let's go.

975
00:30:47,080 --> 00:30:47,440
Let's go.

976
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:49,200
To the next game.

977
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:49,640
Let's move.

978
00:30:51,060 --> 00:31:32,620
(The Truth Season 4 Viewing Calendar)

979
00:32:04,370 --> 00:32:08,370
♪Come now, players all,
let the game of reason start♪

980
00:32:08,370 --> 00:32:12,810
♪Unlock each hidden trial,
let courage spark the dark♪

981
00:32:14,830 --> 00:32:18,990
♪Night falls slow, shadows grow,
the sleuth is lost inside the maze♪

982
00:32:18,990 --> 00:32:23,210
♪Figures pass, lanterns sparse,
dark currents drift without a trace♪

983
00:32:23,210 --> 00:32:26,980
♪Wind picks up, footsteps rush,
cold laughter swallowed by the dark♪

984
00:32:26,980 --> 00:32:31,090
♪Truth concealed, the night
stands still, and nothing leaves a mark♪

985
00:32:31,270 --> 00:32:35,390
♪An unsigned letter, coded words,
the solvers gather one by one♪

986
00:32:35,390 --> 00:32:39,500
♪A broken game, illusion reigns,
who's hiding what they've done?♪

987
00:32:39,500 --> 00:32:43,140
♪Hushed voices, nerves on edge,
wrapped in smoke and mirrors still♪

988
00:32:43,140 --> 00:32:45,270
♪The next second, deeper riddles,
or the answer to the kill♪

989
00:32:45,270 --> 00:32:49,220
♪Every piece of truth
has finally come to light♪

990
00:32:49,460 --> 00:32:53,380
♪Unlock the mystery, turn the question,
let's begin tonight♪

991
00:32:53,590 --> 00:32:57,740
♪Side by side, no holding back,
follow every clue to find the truth♪

992
00:32:57,740 --> 00:33:01,300
♪The story blurs like flowers in fog,
let's begin tonight♪

993
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:06,210
♪Search for the vanished cipher,
trace the proof, and face the sleuth♪
